@page "/teaching/csharp/9-performance"
@inject CourseBook CourseBook;

<CourseModuleIntroduction Module="@CourseBook.CSharpCourse["performance"]">
    <MudText GutterBottom="true">
        C# is a jack-of-all-trades language, and performance is a very important factor for the
        runtime and the BCL. Being a compiled language, it's in a completely different weight class
        than Python for performance, and thanks to sensible generics it gets a major upperhand over
        Java.
    </MudText>
    <MudText GutterBottom="true">
        Even though C# is fast by default, there are many techniques that allow us to squeeze
        out last bits of CPU speed from our code <em>without</em> sacrificing type and memory safety.
        Thanks to advanced tooling measuring and profiling C# is a breeze, and the ever-evolving
        language support for performance critical facilities like <Code>Span</Code> and other ref structs
        gives ample opportunities for optimisation.
    </MudText>
    <MudText GutterBottom="true">
        In the end, C# allows us to ditch memory safety for a while to do pointer-twiddling on stuff
        that requires twiddling pointers. While rarely used in most applications (I've never written production
        code with <Code>unsafe</Code>), in others this is bread-and-butter.
    </MudText>
    <MudText>
        In this module we will learn:
    </MudText>

    <MudList Class="d-block my-4" DisablePadding="true">
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">how to reliably benchmark .NET code;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">
            how to profile C# code with Visual Studio (and alternatives);
        </MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">more details about Garbage Collection;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight"><Code>ref struct</Code>;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight"><Code>Span&lt;T&gt;</Code> and <Code>Memory&lt;T&gt;</Code>;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight"><Code>stackalloc</Code>;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">PLINQ;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">concurrent collections;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight"><Code>unsafe</Code>;</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Filled.ChevronRight">finalizers.</MudListItem>
    </MudList>
</CourseModuleIntroduction>

